{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Cantilever: **Solid Brick**\u2013Frame Coupling visualised in pyGmshViewer\n",
    "\n",
    "Same coupling recipe as the shell version\n",
    "(`example_cantilever_solid_frame_coupling_viewer.ipynb`), but the\n",
    "\"solid\" region is now a genuine 3-D brick (`stdBrick`) mesh. Everything\n",
    "else is identical:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The brick block occupies the left half of the cantilever\n",
    "  ($0 \\le x \\le L_\\text{solid}$)\n",
    "- A master node sits at the interface centroid\n",
    "- **Duplicated nodes** at every interface face-node are rigidly linked\n",
    "  to the master via `rigidLink('beam')`\n",
    "- Each dup node is coupled to its solid partner with `equalDOF`\n",
    "  (translations 1, 2, 3 only \u2014 rotations of the brick nodes stay free)\n",
    "- A single `elasticBeamColumn` runs from master to tip; the load is\n",
    "  applied at the tip\n",
    "\n",
    "Three VTU files are written so the viewer can draw the coupling\n",
    "structure explicitly: the hex mesh, the frame element, and each\n",
    "rigid-link spoke."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometry\n",
    "L       = 10.0      # total cantilever length [m]\n",
    "h       = 1.0       # depth   (y) [m]\n",
    "b       = 0.5       # width   (z) [m]\n",
    "L_solid = L / 2.0\n",
    "L_frame = L / 2.0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Material\n",
    "E   = 30.0e6        # kPa\n",
    "nu  = 0.2\n",
    "G   = E / (2.0 * (1.0 + nu))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loading\n",
    "P   = -100.0        # tip load [kN], downward (-y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mesh density (bricks)\n",
    "nx_s, ny_s, nz_s = 20, 6, 3\n",
    "dx = L_solid / nx_s\n",
    "dy = h       / ny_s\n",
    "dz = b       / nz_s\n",
    "\n",
    "# Frame cross-section (b x h rectangle)\n",
    "A  = b * h\n",
    "Iz = b * h**3 / 12.0\n",
    "Iy = h * b**3 / 12.0\n",
    "J  = 0.5 * (Iy + Iz)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Solid brick block : {nx_s}x{ny_s}x{nz_s} = {nx_s*ny_s*nz_s} elements')\n",
    "print(f'EI (in-plane)     : {E*Iz:.3e} kN\u00b7m\u00b2')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Build the model\n",
    "\n",
    "The solid block is created in an `ndf=3` builder because `stdBrick`\n",
    "uses translational DOFs only. We then switch to `ndf=6` for the\n",
    "master / tip / dup nodes so `rigidLink('beam')` and\n",
    "`elasticBeamColumn` have the rotational DOFs they need."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.wipe()\n",
    "ops.model('basic', '-ndm', 3, '-ndf', 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# \u2500\u2500 nDMaterial for the bricks \u2500\u2500\n",
    "ops.nDMaterial('ElasticIsotropic', 1, E, nu)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.1 Solid (brick) nodes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "solid_nodes = {}    # (i, j, k) -> node_tag\n",
    "nid = 0\n",
    "for k in range(nz_s + 1):\n",
    "    for j in range(ny_s + 1):\n",
    "        for i in range(nx_s + 1):\n",
    "            nid += 1\n",
    "            x = i * dx\n",
    "            y = -h / 2.0 + j * dy\n",
    "            z = -b / 2.0 + k * dz\n",
    "            ops.node(nid, x, y, z)\n",
    "            solid_nodes[(i, j, k)] = nid\n",
    "\n",
    "n_solid_nodes = nid\n",
    "\n",
    "# Full cantilever fixity at x = 0\n",
    "for k in range(nz_s + 1):\n",
    "    for j in range(ny_s + 1):\n",
    "        tag = solid_nodes[(0, j, k)]\n",
    "        ops.fix(tag, 1, 1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Interface face (x = L_solid, i = nx_s): one node per (j, k)\n",
    "interface_solid_tags = [\n",
    "    solid_nodes[(nx_s, j, k)]\n",
    "    for k in range(nz_s + 1)\n",
    "    for j in range(ny_s + 1)\n",
    "]\n",
    "print(f'Solid nodes     : {n_solid_nodes}')\n",
    "print(f'Interface face  : {len(interface_solid_tags)} nodes')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 Master + tip nodes (on the beam axis)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Switch to 6 DOFs for frame + coupling nodes\n",
    "ops.model('basic', '-ndm', 3, '-ndf', 6)\n",
    "\n",
    "master_tag = n_solid_nodes + 1\n",
    "tip_tag    = n_solid_nodes + 2\n",
    "\n",
    "ops.node(master_tag, L_solid, 0.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(tip_tag,    L,       0.0, 0.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Master : {master_tag} @ ({L_solid}, 0, 0)')\n",
    "print(f'Tip    : {tip_tag} @ ({L}, 0, 0)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.3 Duplicated interface nodes\n",
    "\n",
    "One dup node sits at each interface face-node position. `rigidLink`\n",
    "drags them with the master; `equalDOF` passes translations through to\n",
    "the brick face-nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dup_tags = []\n",
    "next_id = tip_tag + 1\n",
    "for sn in interface_solid_tags:\n",
    "    c = ops.nodeCoord(sn)\n",
    "    ops.node(next_id, *c)\n",
    "    dup_tags.append(next_id)\n",
    "    next_id += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Duplicated nodes : {dup_tags[0]}..{dup_tags[-1]} ({len(dup_tags)} total)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Elements"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3.1 \u2500\u2500 Brick elements \u2500\u2500 stdBrick = 8-node linear isoparametric\n",
    "eid = 0\n",
    "brick_elements = []\n",
    "for k in range(nz_s):\n",
    "    for j in range(ny_s):\n",
    "        for i in range(nx_s):\n",
    "            eid += 1\n",
    "            n0 = solid_nodes[(i,   j,   k)]\n",
    "            n1 = solid_nodes[(i+1, j,   k)]\n",
    "            n2 = solid_nodes[(i+1, j+1, k)]\n",
    "            n3 = solid_nodes[(i,   j+1, k)]\n",
    "            n4 = solid_nodes[(i,   j,   k+1)]\n",
    "            n5 = solid_nodes[(i+1, j,   k+1)]\n",
    "            n6 = solid_nodes[(i+1, j+1, k+1)]\n",
    "            n7 = solid_nodes[(i,   j+1, k+1)]\n",
    "            ops.element('stdBrick', eid,\n",
    "                        n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5, n6, n7, 1)\n",
    "            brick_elements.append((eid, n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5, n6, n7))\n",
    "n_brick = eid\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3.2 \u2500\u2500 Frame element \u2500\u2500\n",
    "ops.geomTransf('Linear', 1, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0)\n",
    "eid += 1\n",
    "frame_eid = eid\n",
    "ops.element('elasticBeamColumn', eid, master_tag, tip_tag,\n",
    "            A, E, G, J, Iy, Iz, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Brick elements : {n_brick}')\n",
    "print(f'Frame element  : {frame_eid}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Coupling constraints\n",
    "\n",
    "Same two-step recipe as the shell version:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **A.** `rigidLink('beam')` from master to every dup node \u2014 6-DOF rigid-body\n",
    "- **B.** `equalDOF(dup, solid, 1, 2, 3)` \u2014 translations only, so brick\n",
    "  face-nodes inherit the rigid-body motion while keeping their\n",
    "  rotations fixed (see Section 2.1)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for dn in dup_tags:\n",
    "    ops.rigidLink('beam', master_tag, dn)\n",
    "\n",
    "for dn, sn in zip(dup_tags, interface_solid_tags):\n",
    "    ops.equalDOF(dn, sn, 1, 2, 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'rigidLinks : {len(dup_tags)} (master -> dup)')\n",
    "print(f'equalDOFs  : {len(dup_tags)} (dup -> brick face, DOFs 1/2/3)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Loading & analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.timeSeries('Linear', 1)\n",
    "ops.pattern('Plain', 1, 1)\n",
    "ops.load(tip_tag, 0.0, float(P), 0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Chained MPCs (master -> dup -> solid) are handled robustly with Penalty\n",
    "ops.constraints('Penalty', 1.0e12, 1.0e12)\n",
    "ops.numberer('RCM')\n",
    "ops.system('UmfPack')\n",
    "ops.test('NormDispIncr', 1.0e-8, 30, 0)\n",
    "ops.algorithm('Linear')\n",
    "ops.integrator('LoadControl', 1.0)\n",
    "ops.analysis('Static')\n",
    "\n",
    "ok = ops.analyze(1)\n",
    "print('analyze ok =', ok)\n",
    "print(f'tip uy = {ops.nodeDisp(tip_tag, 2):.4e} m')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. Viewer export\n",
    "\n",
    "As in the shell example, we export three separate VTU files:\n",
    "\n",
    "| File                              | Cells             |\n",
    "|----------------------------------|-------------------|\n",
    "| `brick_coupling_solid.vtu`       | `VTK_HEXAHEDRON`  |\n",
    "| `brick_coupling_frame.vtu`       | `VTK_LINE`        |\n",
    "| `brick_coupling_rigid_links.vtu` | `VTK_LINE`        |\n",
    "\n",
    "All share a `Displacement` vector field, so toggling **Show Deformed**\n",
    "in the viewer moves them together."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6.1 \u2500\u2500 Assemble the solid (brick) arrays \u2500\u2500\n",
    "tags_sorted = sorted(solid_nodes.values())\n",
    "tag_to_row  = {t: r for r, t in enumerate(tags_sorted)}\n",
    "\n",
    "solid_points = np.zeros((len(tags_sorted), 3))\n",
    "solid_disp   = np.zeros((len(tags_sorted), 3))\n",
    "for (i, j, k), tag in solid_nodes.items():\n",
    "    row = tag_to_row[tag]\n",
    "    solid_points[row] = (i*dx, -h/2.0 + j*dy, -b/2.0 + k*dz)\n",
    "    d = ops.nodeDisp(tag)\n",
    "    solid_disp[row] = (d[0], d[1], d[2])\n",
    "\n",
    "solid_cells = np.array(\n",
    "    [[tag_to_row[n0], tag_to_row[n1], tag_to_row[n2], tag_to_row[n3],\n",
    "      tag_to_row[n4], tag_to_row[n5], tag_to_row[n6], tag_to_row[n7]]\n",
    "     for (_, n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5, n6, n7) in brick_elements],\n",
    "    dtype=np.int32,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f'Solid brick mesh : {len(tags_sorted)} nodes, {len(solid_cells)} hex')\n",
    "print(f'  |u| max        : {np.linalg.norm(solid_disp, axis=1).max():.4e} m')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6.2 \u2500\u2500 Frame line \u2500\u2500\n",
    "master_xyz = np.array(ops.nodeCoord(master_tag)); master_d = np.array(ops.nodeDisp(master_tag))[:3]\n",
    "tip_xyz    = np.array(ops.nodeCoord(tip_tag));    tip_d    = np.array(ops.nodeDisp(tip_tag))[:3]\n",
    "\n",
    "frame_points = np.vstack([master_xyz, tip_xyz])\n",
    "frame_disp   = np.vstack([master_d, tip_d])\n",
    "frame_cells  = np.array([[0, 1]], dtype=np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 6.3 \u2500\u2500 Rigid-link lines (master -> each dup node) \u2500\u2500\n",
    "n_dup = len(dup_tags)\n",
    "links_points = np.zeros((1 + n_dup, 3))\n",
    "links_disp   = np.zeros((1 + n_dup, 3))\n",
    "links_points[0] = master_xyz\n",
    "links_disp[0]   = master_d\n",
    "for k, dn in enumerate(dup_tags):\n",
    "    c = ops.nodeCoord(dn)\n",
    "    d = ops.nodeDisp(dn)\n",
    "    links_points[k+1] = c\n",
    "    links_disp[k+1]   = d[:3]\n",
    "links_cells = np.array([[0, k+1] for k in range(n_dup)], dtype=np.int32)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Rigid links : {n_dup} spokes from master')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6.4 \u2500\u2500 Write VTU files \u2500\u2500\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '../src')\n",
    "from pyGmsh.VTKExport import write_vtu\n",
    "\n",
    "VTK_HEXAHEDRON = 12\n",
    "VTK_LINE       = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "solid_vtu = Path('brick_coupling_solid.vtu').resolve()\n",
    "frame_vtu = Path('brick_coupling_frame.vtu').resolve()\n",
    "links_vtu = Path('brick_coupling_rigid_links.vtu').resolve()\n",
    "\n",
    "write_vtu(\n",
    "    solid_vtu, points=solid_points, cells=solid_cells,\n",
    "    vtk_cell_type=VTK_HEXAHEDRON,\n",
    "    point_data={\n",
    "        'Displacement': solid_disp,\n",
    "        '|U|':          np.linalg.norm(solid_disp, axis=1),\n",
    "        'Ux':           solid_disp[:, 0],\n",
    "        'Uy':           solid_disp[:, 1],\n",
    "        'Uz':           solid_disp[:, 2],\n",
    "    },\n",
    ")\n",
    "write_vtu(\n",
    "    frame_vtu, points=frame_points, cells=frame_cells,\n",
    "    vtk_cell_type=VTK_LINE,\n",
    "    point_data={'Displacement': frame_disp,\n",
    "                '|U|': np.linalg.norm(frame_disp, axis=1)},\n",
    ")\n",
    "write_vtu(\n",
    "    links_vtu, points=links_points, cells=links_cells,\n",
    "    vtk_cell_type=VTK_LINE,\n",
    "    point_data={'Displacement': links_disp,\n",
    "                '|U|': np.linalg.norm(links_disp, axis=1)},\n",
    ")\n",
    "print('Wrote:')\n",
    "for p in (solid_vtu, frame_vtu, links_vtu):\n",
    "    print(' ', p.name)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6.5 \u2500\u2500 Launch pyGmshViewer \u2500\u2500\n",
    "# Install once: pip install -e \".[viewer]\"  from the repo root\n",
    "from pyGmshViewer import show\n",
    "\n",
    "show(solid_vtu, frame_vtu, links_vtu, blocking=False)\n",
    "print('Viewer launched. Recommended interaction:')\n",
    "print('  1. Select brick_coupling_solid in the Model tree')\n",
    "print('  2. Controls \u2192 Contour: |U| (Viridis)')\n",
    "print('  3. Controls \u2192 Deformation: Show Deformed, scale 50-100x')\n",
    "print('  4. The frame (amber line) and rigid links (amber spokes) will')\n",
    "print('     now render as thick tubes \u2014 you can watch each spoke rotate')\n",
    "print('     around the master as the bending kinematics develops')\n",
    "print('  5. Tools \u2192 Point Probe (Ctrl+P) on the interface face nodes to')\n",
    "print('     verify equalDOF couples their translations to each dup node')"
   ]
  }
 ],
